I"<h1 id="step-3-choose-a-os-for-your-pinephone">Step 3: Choose a OS for your PinePhone</h1>

<h2 id="ubports">UBports</h2>
<p>UBPorts is a community fork and continuation of Ubuntu Touch.
Minimum SD Card Size: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">16GB</code></p>

<p>It features:</p>
<ul>
  <li>A read only root filesystem to make it reliable and easily updatable.</li>
  <li>Convergence - A way to run desktop apps on PinePhone. (YMMV on scaling)</li>
  <li>A simple easy to use UI.</li>
</ul>

<p>Download Link:</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>https://ci.ubports.com/job/rootfs/job/rootfs-pinephone-systemimage/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/ubuntu-touch-pinephone.img.xz
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>You will first need to extract this with 7zip or any other archiving tool to get a .img</p>

<p><a href="https://gitlab.com/ubports/community-ports/pinephone/-/issues">UBports PinePhone Issue Tracker</a></p>

